SLS 26RS-2254 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 102
BY SENATOR BASS
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH. Designates Tuesday, May 5, 2026, as Literacy Day at the
Louisiana State Capitol and recognizes The Center for Literacy & Learning for its leadership
in advancing literacy statewide.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate Tuesday, May 5, 2026, as Literacy Day at the Louisiana State Capitol and to
3 recognize The Center for Literacy & Learning for its leadership in advancing literacy
4 statewide.
5 WHEREAS, studies have shown that students who do not read proficiently by the
6 end of third grade are four times more likely to drop out of school and those students who
7 lack basic reading proficiency are nearly six times more likely to leave school without
8 earning a diploma; and
9 WHEREAS, dyslexia, a specific learning disability that affects as many as one in five
10 individuals, presents a significant barrier to reading success without proper support; and
11 WHEREAS, literacy is foundational to a student's academic success, long-term
12 opportunity, and personal empowerment; and
13 WHEREAS, a study, in 2022, found that seventy-two percent of Louisiana's fourth
14 grade students did not read proficiently, placing the state forty-second in the nation for
15 fourth grade reading achievement; and
16 WHEREAS, in 2024, Louisiana made historic progress by climbing twenty-six
17 places in national ranking and now ranks sixteenth in the nation for fourth grade reading,
18 according to the National Assessment of Educational Progress; and
