1 WHEREAS, The Center for Literacy & Learning, founded in 1992, has for the past
2 thirty-three years implemented evidence-based instructional and coaching practices that
3 improve teaching and increase student learning outcomes from birth to twelfth grade; and
4 WHEREAS, the center draws on over three hundred fifty combined years of
5 professional education experience, focusing on closing the achievement gap through
6 targeted, high-quality professional development for educators of at-risk students; and
7 WHEREAS, The Center for Literacy & Learning employs a comprehensive literacy
8 wraparound approach, providing services to educators, families, and communities that
9 support learning both inside and outside the classroom; and
10 WHEREAS, over the past seven years the center has successfully advocated for the
11 creation of instrumental commissions that have shaped the state's literacy policies, including
12 the Early Literacy Commission and the Louisiana Literacy Advisory Commission; and
13 WHEREAS, in partnership with the Louisiana Department of Education, the center
14 launched the Literacy Coaching Program in 2020; and
15 WHEREAS, improving literacy across Louisiana is vital to building a strong
16 workforce, creating high-quality jobs, and sustaining long-term economic growth.
17 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
18 does hereby designate Tuesday, May 5, 2026, as Literacy Day at the Louisiana State Capitol,
19 does hereby commend the dedicated work of The Center for Literacy & Learning, and does
20 hereby celebrate the notable progress in fourth grade literacy scores in Louisiana.
21 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to The
22 Center for Literacy & Learning.
